### Step 1 — Login
POST {{host}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "admin",
  "password": "admin"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("token", response.body.token);
  client.global.set("run", String(Date.now()));
%}

###

### Step 2 — Create customer (individual)
# CPF is a fixed valid Brazilian CPF — re-run requires a clean DB or a different CPF
POST {{host}}/party
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "personType": "INDIVIDUAL",
  "cpf": "52998224725",
  "legalName": "Maria Consignment {{run}}",
  "name": "Maria {{run}}",
  "customer": true,
  "supplier": false,
  "salesperson": false
}

> {%
  client.global.set("customerId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 3 — Create salesperson
# CPF is a fixed valid Brazilian CPF — re-run requires a clean DB or a different CPF
POST {{host}}/party
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "personType": "INDIVIDUAL",
  "cpf": "71428793860",
  "legalName": "Vendedor Consignment {{run}}",
  "name": "Vendedor {{run}}",
  "customer": false,
  "supplier": false,
  "salesperson": true,
  "commissionPercent": 5.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("salespersonId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 4 — Create brand
POST {{host}}/catalog/brands
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Consignment Brand {{run}}"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("brandId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 5 — Create category
POST {{host}}/catalog/categories
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Consignment Category {{run}}",
  "parentId": null
}

> {%
  client.global.set("categoryId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 6 — Create size
POST {{host}}/catalog/sizes
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "M"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("sizeId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 7 — Create product with 2 SKUs (implantationQty=30 and implantationQty=20)
# Barcodes use $uuid to avoid unique-constraint conflicts on re-runs
# ProductSkuCreated → seeds stock_balance for each SKU
POST {{host}}/catalog/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Consignment Shirt {{run}}",
  "price": 150.00,
  "cost": 70.00,
  "purchaseDate": null,
  "colorId": null,
  "brandId": "{{brandId}}",
  "categoryId": "{{categoryId}}",
  "skus": [
    {
      "barcode": "{{$uuid}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 30
    },
    {
      "barcode": "{{$uuid}}",
      "sizeId": "{{sizeId}}",
      "implantationQty": 20
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("productId", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("skuId1", response.body.skus[0].id);
  client.global.set("skuId2", response.body.skus[1].id);
%}

###

### Step 8 — Verify initial stock balance for SKU 1 (currentBalance=30)
# Served from Elasticsearch
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 9 — Verify initial stock balance for SKU 2 (currentBalance=20)
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 10 — Issue consignment: 5 units of SKU 1 + 3 units of SKU 2
# ConsignmentIssued → ConsignmentIssuedListener → RecordConsignmentIssueStockUseCase
#   SKU 1: balance 30 → 25 (CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE, qty=-5)
#   SKU 2: balance 20 → 17 (CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE, qty=-3)
POST {{host}}/consignments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "{{customerId}}",
  "salespersonIds": ["{{salespersonId}}"],
  "issueDate": "2026-05-12",
  "notes": "Consignment flow test {{run}}",
  "items": [
    {
      "skuId": "{{skuId1}}",
      "productId": "{{productId}}",
      "quantity": 5,
      "unitPrice": 150.00
    },
    {
      "skuId": "{{skuId2}}",
      "productId": "{{productId}}",
      "quantity": 3,
      "unitPrice": 150.00
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("consignmentId", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("itemId1", response.body.items[0].id);
  client.global.set("itemId2", response.body.items[1].id);
%}

###

### Step 11 — Verify stock decreased after issue: SKU 1 (currentBalance=25)
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 12 — Verify stock decreased after issue: SKU 2 (currentBalance=17)
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 13 — Get consignment from Elasticsearch index (status=OPEN)
# Served from Elasticsearch — reflects ConsignmentIssued event
GET {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 14 — Check movement history for SKU 1 (2 entries: CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE qty=-5, INITIAL_STOCK qty=30)
GET {{host}}/inventory/movements/{{skuId1}}?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 15 — Partial return: return 2 units of SKU 1
# ConsignmentItemsReturned → ConsignmentItemsReturnedListener → RecordConsignmentReturnStockUseCase
#   SKU 1: balance 25 → 27 (CONSIGNMENT_RETURN, qty=+2)
POST {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}/return-items
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "skuId": "{{skuId1}}",
      "quantityReturned": 2
    }
  ]
}

###

### Step 16 — Verify stock increased after return: SKU 1 (currentBalance=27)
# quantityIssued=5, quantityReturned=2 → 3 still out on consignment
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 17 — Verify SKU 2 balance unchanged after partial return (currentBalance=17)
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 18 — Get updated consignment from Elasticsearch (quantityReturned for SKU 1 = 2)
GET {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 19 — Check movement history for SKU 1 (3 entries: CONSIGNMENT_RETURN, CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE, INITIAL_STOCK)
GET {{host}}/inventory/movements/{{skuId1}}?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 20 — Close consignment: sold items generate a sale
# quantitySold = quantityIssued - quantityReturned
#   SKU 1: sold 3 (5 issued - 2 returned); SKU 2: sold 3 (3 issued - 0 returned)
# Total = 3×150 + 3×150 = 900.00
POST {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}/close
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sellerIds": [{{salespersonId}}],
  "installments": [
    {
      "paymentModality": "PIX",
      "dueDate": "2026-05-12",
      "amount": 900.00
    }
  ]
}

> {%
  client.global.set("saleId", response.body.id);
%}

###

### Step 20a — GET /sales/{saleId} — verify the sale created from consignment close
# origin should be CONSIGNMENT, consignmentId should match
GET {{host}}/sales/{{saleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 21 — Verify consignment status is CLOSED in Elasticsearch
GET {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 22 — Search consignments by customerId (should include the closed consignment)
GET {{host}}/consignments?customerId={{customerId}}&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 23 — Search consignments filtered by status=CLOSED
GET {{host}}/consignments?status=CLOSED&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 24 — Search consignments filtered by status=OPEN (should not include this consignment)
GET {{host}}/consignments?status=OPEN&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 25 — Search consignments filtered by salespersonId
GET {{host}}/consignments?salespersonId={{salespersonId}}&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 26 — Search consignments by date range
GET {{host}}/consignments?from=2026-05-12&to=2026-05-12&page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 27 — Verify final stock balances reflect all operations
# SKU 1: 30 (initial) - 5 (issued) + 2 (returned) = 27
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 28 — Verify final stock balance for SKU 2
# SKU 2: 20 (initial) - 3 (issued) = 17 (no returns)
GET {{host}}/inventory/balance/{{skuId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 29 — Final movement history for SKU 1 (3 entries: CONSIGNMENT_RETURN qty=+2, CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE qty=-5, INITIAL_STOCK qty=30)
GET {{host}}/inventory/movements/{{skuId1}}?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Step 30 — Final movement history for SKU 2 (2 entries: CONSIGNMENT_ISSUE qty=-3, INITIAL_STOCK qty=20)
GET {{host}}/inventory/movements/{{skuId2}}?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### --- Error cases ---

### Step 31 — Try to close already-closed consignment → 422 Unprocessable Entity
POST {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}/close
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sellerIds": [{{salespersonId}}],
  "installments": [
    {
      "paymentMethod": "PIX",
      "amount": 100.00
    }
  ]
}

###

### Step 32 — Try to return items from closed consignment → 422 Unprocessable Entity
POST {{host}}/consignments/{{consignmentId}}/return-items
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "skuId": "{{skuId1}}",
      "quantityReturned": 1
    }
  ]
}

###

### Step 33 — Issue consignment with unknown customer → 404 Not Found
POST {{host}}/consignments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "999999999",
  "salespersonIds": ["{{salespersonId}}"],
  "issueDate": "2026-05-12",
  "notes": "Should fail",
  "items": [
    {
      "skuId": "{{skuId1}}",
      "productId": "{{productId}}",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 150.00
    }
  ]
}

###

### Step 34 — Get non-existent consignment → 404 Not Found
GET {{host}}/consignments/999999999
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
